  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" comedy movie ever is highly subjective and varies based on personal taste, cultural background, and comedic style. However, several films are frequently cited as some of the greatest comedies of all time. Notable mentions include:\n\n1. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)** - A cult classic known for its absurd humor and iconic quotes.\n2. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)** - A classic starring Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon, renowned for its witty dialogue and cross-dressing plot.\n3. **\"Groundhog Day\" (1993)** - A unique take on the romantic comedy genre with a philosophical twist.\n4. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)** - A parody of disaster films filled with puns and slapstick humor.\n5. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)** - A Coen Brothers film that has gained a massive following for its quirky characters and offbeat humor.\n\nUltimately, the best comedy movie is the one that resonates most with you personally. What are some of your favorite comedies?",
